data.chText: （通常为无定形的）块
data.enText: a piece of sth hard or solid, usually without a particular shape

data.chText: 一块煤 / 奶酪 / 木头
data.enText: a lump of coal/cheese/wood

data.chText: 这调味汁里有结块。
data.enText: This sauce has lumps in it.

data.chText: 加一块方糖还是两块？
data.enText: One lump or two?

data.chText: 肿块；隆起
data.enText: a swelling under the skin, sometimes a sign of serious illness

data.chText: 除了头上起了个包，他没有别的伤。
data.enText: He was unhurt apart from a lump on his head.

data.chText: 每月要检查一次乳房是否有肿块。
data.enText: Check your breasts for lumps every month.

data.chText: 笨重的人；懒汉；傻大个
data.enText: a heavy, lazy or stupid person
have, etc. a lump in your throat

data.chText: （因愤怒或情绪激动而）喉咙哽住，哽咽
data.enText: to feel pressure in the throat because you are very angry or emotional
take your lumps

data.chText: 毫无怨言地忍受
data.enText: to accept bad things that happen to you without complaining

data.chText: 把…归并一起（或合起来考虑）
data.enText: to put or consider different things together in the same group

data.chText: 你不能把所有的亚洲语言混为一谈。
data.enText: You can't lump all Asian languages together.
lump it

data.chText: （因别无选择而）勉强接受，将就，勉为其难
data.enText: to accept sth unpleasant because there's no other choice

data.chText: 你不满意我很抱歉，可你只好将就一点了。
data.enText: I'm sorry you're not happy about it but you'll just have to lump it.

data.chText: 情况就是这样——不管你高兴还是不高兴！
data.enText: That's the situation─ like it or lump it !

trans: 把…归并在一起；把…混到一块儿

example: a ball of mud caught him on the shoulder

tr: a large piece of something without definite shape
an abnormal protuberance or localized enlargement
group or chunk together in a certain order or place side by side

value.def: A lump of something is a solid piece of it.

example.ex: The potter shaped and squeezed the lump of clay into a graceful shape.
example.tran: 制陶工人把黏土块捏塑成优美的形状。

example.ex: They used to buy ten kilos of beef in one lump.
example.tran: 他们过去常买10公斤重的整块牛肉。

value.def: A lump on or in someone's body is a small, hard swelling that has been caused by an injury or an illness.

example.ex: I've got a lump on my shoulder...
Howard had to have cancer surgery for a lump in his chest.
example.tran: 霍华德不得不进行肿瘤手术以切除胸部的肿块。

value.def: A lump of sugar is a small cube of it.

example.ex: ...a nugget of rough gold about the size of a lump of sugar...
example.tran: 一块方糖般大小的粗金

example.ex: 'No sugar,' I said, and Jim asked for two lumps.
example.tran: “不加糖，”我说道。吉姆则要了两块。

value.def: If you say that someone will have to lump it, you mean that they must accept a situation or decision whether they like it or not.

example.ex: The crew will be sleeping in the hull and will have to lump it...
example.tran: 船员将睡在船舱里，不乐意也没办法。

example.ex: William was going to kick up a fuss, but he realized he'd have to lump it.
example.tran: 威廉本想要大闹一番，却意识到自己只能忍下这口气。

value.tran: 只得忍气吞声；不得不忍受

value.def: If you say that you have a lump in your throat, you mean that you have a tight feeling in your throat because of a strong emotion such as sorrow or gratitude.

example.ex: I stood there with a lump in my throat and tried to fight back tears...
example.tran: 我站在那里，喉咙哽塞，拼命想止住眼泪。

example.ex: It was a great reception and it brought a lump to my throat.
example.tran: 如此盛情接待，叫我一时哽咽。
